Among other things, there was evidence of a much more active Iraqi nuclear program in recent years than almost anyone had thought. It is possible that Saddam already has one or two usable devices. He certainly has large stocks of gas and bio-agents. <br>
The mobile bio-labs, carried in truck convoys, are a potential nuclear target. There is simply no other way to simultaneously destroy the labs and reliably sterilize the large amounts of bio-war organisms that would escape containment as a result of the attack. A saturation napalm attack(hundreds if not thousands of tons) might do it, but I wouldn't bet the farm on that, and there is a lot more than a farm at stake here. Saddam does not care if his own people are infected, he would count that as a bonus since his western sympathizers would blame the US for it. Indeed, the critical need to sterilize bio-weapons stocks may be a factor in all the recent talk about nuclear weapons. My prediction: low air burst by a specially developed 5-10 kt weapon above the convoys or their hideouts.<br>
Two points on the credibility of Powell's claims:<br>
1.The Bush gang are headed for impeachment and jail if they fail to produce the hands-on proof after a war, and they know it.<br>
2. Senator Joe Biden, a major opposition leader and Iraq war skeptic, is now completely convinced:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> If I had this evidence before a jury that was an unbiased jury, I could get a conviction,” said Sen. Joe Biden of Delaware, top Democrat on the Senate Foreign Relations Committee. “But we’re talking about a different stage. (Powell) has a tougher jury and there is a lot of skepticism that exists in the international community.” <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.littlegreenfootballs.com/weblog/?entry=5482#comments">Little Green Footballs</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> has started a string on this. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A> at: 2/5/03 11:46:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1960<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/5/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/zaphod3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: War it is</span><hr size=1> If it comes to war, then let's hope they do it right... overwhelmingly <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 829<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/5/03 2:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: War it is</span><hr size=1> Interesting point about the risks inherent in destroying bio-weapons labs.  I'm assuming they'll try to leave suspected labs untouched but if it does become necessary to destroy them a tactical nuclear strike might be the safest option.  Hopefully it doesn't come to that.  I have to say I'm not very gunho about invading Iraq but I agree with Zaphod, a quick and overwhelming response is probably our best bet to insure that Saddam doesn't have much time to contemplate using any chemical or biological weps he may have.    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 2/5/03 2:14:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 3237<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/5/03 7:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: War it is</span><hr size=1> You would think the US would have a few undercover agents planted over the years. The evidence doesn't look exactly overwhelming but hopefully the UN will buy it. I hope it isn't fabricated. I think war is utterly unavoidable now no matter what. Saddam might say he is going to comply now in another effort to stall but Bush won't have it. He's sending in the troops and I know both Britain and Australia will follow.<br>
I've always held that human ingenuity should never be underestimated. Even the experts have doubted the possibility of Saddam having any nukes yet. They couldn't see how he could have aquired them. Less advanced nation make up for a lack of available technology with resourcefulness. N.Korea dealt with Pakistan secretly and there's no telling how many nations Iraq has approached. Iraq has some good scientists. It would surprise me if they didn't have atleast one nuke. <br>
<br>
It's probably buried deep near the boarder to Turkey awaiting US forces. If used, an Iraqi nuke would trigger several US nukes in a retalliatory action. Meanwhile Saddam will probably be safely hidden away waiting for the americans to get tired and leave. They might have to police the country for years. That would be expensive and difficult in a nation which by all accounts hates the US. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=370.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=370.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=370.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.threadControl?topicID=370.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=370.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=370.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving